<br>
I spent a while on Kerra Isle soaking up the local flavor, wrote a story about it. I liked it -- kind of restful, since I was killing wharf rats and raising faction with them rather than slaughtering cats. It made me decide to take Lest in a new direction -- one where he, as an outsider, tends to truck with critters often considered prey by players -- Kerrans, Aviaks, stuff that doesn't attack a half-elf on site, basically, but are easy to make enemies. <br>
<br>
Anyone know how easy it is to sod up your faction with NPCs that aren't, say, orcs or goblins that attack on site? <br>
<br>
Double reason I'm asking -- I started a bard a few days ago on that damnable second account I couldn't resist using, partially because I wanted to force myself to group (rolled a Vah Shir beastlord last week and realized I might end up falling back on my unfortunate tendency to be a loner) and partially because I think I can make up an intense backstory. Thing is I rolled agnostic, and am now curious how badly rerolling as Veeshan worshipping would screw with faction and, well, I've killed a dozen orc pawns already but would like to infiltrate Neriak some day with the help of a Mask. Should I reroll and relocate, or will less than 15 marks against me with the Indigo Brotherhood be curable with a mask of deception and the faction song? <br>
<br>
Thanks in advance,<br>
Lest Ravenfolly<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 692<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/17/02 11:42:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2349.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: exploring places without faction killing you?</span><hr size=1> Indigo Brotherhood isn't the Neriak Guards, it's just the warrior guild.  <br>
<br>
Even if you're horribly KOS to the brotherhood you can still wander about the city at leisure if you're okay with the other factions (just don't walk into the warrior guild).<br>
<br>
The guards are on Dreadguard Inner, Dreadguard Outer, and the Dead (Necro/SK guild) factions.<br>
<br>
